{"video_id": "408qlS2z6ys", "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=408qlS2z6ys", "title": "408qlS2z6ys", "category": "Unknown Category", "fps": null, "segments": [{"start": 0.4, "end": 7.140000000000001, "text": "Welcome to my video. The subject here is going to be optocouplers theory operation and circuits."}, {"start": 7.92, "end": 15.0, "text": "I'm your host, Lewis Laughlin. Visit my website at www.bristolwatch.com."}, {"start": 16.44, "end": 26.54, "text": "Objective to understand the basic operation of optocouplers, their types, and use in power control circuits with Arduino and PIC, etc."}, {"start": 26.54, "end": 32.22, "text": "There will be a couple of short live video clips at the end of this presentation."}, {"start": 33.92, "end": 45.480000000000004, "text": "A typical optocoupler is usually a 6-pin device that has generally an LED infrared emitter and some type of light sensor."}, {"start": 46.22, "end": 50.36, "text": "If we turn on the LED, it turns on the light sensor."}, {"start": 50.36, "end": 56.06, "text": "The light sensor can be a transistor or it can be any number of things."}, {"start": 57.38, "end": 64.36, "text": "The big advantage of optocouplers is electrical and noise isolation."}, {"start": 65.53999999999999, "end": 70.12, "text": "The isolation potential can go up into thousands of volts."}, {"start": 71.02, "end": 76.18, "text": "Some of them are rated at 7,000 or 10,000 volts electrical isolation."}, {"start": 76.18, "end": 81.16000000000001, "text": "As shown here, it can be a number of detectors."}, {"start": 82.12, "end": 84.66000000000001, "text": "It could be a light activated SCR."}, {"start": 84.80000000000001, "end": 86.10000000000001, "text": "It could be a digital output."}, {"start": 86.36000000000001, "end": 88.14000000000001, "text": "It could be a Darlington transistor."}, {"start": 88.44000000000001, "end": 90.78, "text": "There's all kinds of detectors."}, {"start": 91.5, "end": 94.04, "text": "But they all have the basic same purpose."}, {"start": 94.34, "end": 97.7, "text": "Voltage isolation between input and output."}, {"start": 97.7, "end": 109.24000000000001, "text": "For example, this part number, H11AA1, has dual back-to-back infrared emitters."}, {"start": 109.48, "end": 115.84, "text": "Quite handy for making things such as a zero crossing detector."}, {"start": 115.84, "end": 128.48000000000002, "text": "Sometimes we will use optocouplers in conjunction with secondary components to make solid-state relays."}, {"start": 128.48, "end": 132.67999999999998, "text": "What you're seeing pictured here is an input protection circuit."}, {"start": 132.95999999999998, "end": 135.66, "text": "It can work with any of these optocouplers."}, {"start": 136.34, "end": 139.82, "text": "They can have a range from 3 to 30 volts."}, {"start": 139.82, "end": 149.78, "text": "Either though the LED itself has a rating of probably 1.2 to 1.8 volts,"}, {"start": 150.57999999999998, "end": 159.16, "text": "the addition of this 2-watt resistor and Q1, which is an NPN transistor like a 2N2222,"}, {"start": 159.84, "end": 165.48, "text": "as the voltage increases, the current flow will increase through the LED."}, {"start": 165.48, "end": 171.51999999999998, "text": "And of course, it creates a larger voltage drop across this 47-ohm resistor,"}, {"start": 172.39999999999998, "end": 179.5, "text": "cutting this transistor Q1 on and shunting the current through Q1 instead of the LED."}, {"start": 180.16, "end": 182.35999999999999, "text": "That's how your protection circuit works."}, {"start": 183.5, "end": 188.22, "text": "This is your very most basic optocoupler circuit."}, {"start": 190.22, "end": 195.28, "text": "Generally, we tie the LED through a resistor to ground."}, {"start": 195.48, "end": 200.95999999999998, "text": "And connect it to generally an I.O. pin of an Arduino, PIC, or whatever."}, {"start": 201.79999999999998, "end": 206.45999999999998, "text": "A high, of course, 5 volts or 3 or whatever you're using,"}, {"start": 207.07999999999998, "end": 208.76, "text": "turns the LED on."}, {"start": 209.28, "end": 213.48, "text": "The LED light onto the base of an internal phototransistor"}, {"start": 214.06, "end": 218.88, "text": "cuts on the phototransistor and completing a path to ground."}, {"start": 218.88, "end": 227.57999999999998, "text": "This circuit is fine, except it suffers from low-power handling capabilities."}, {"start": 228.0, "end": 231.35999999999999, "text": "Optocouplers are generally low-power devices."}, {"start": 232.04, "end": 237.2, "text": "So we have to look into using optocouplers to control more powerful devices"}, {"start": 237.2, "end": 241.73999999999998, "text": "to really handle heavy jobs."}, {"start": 241.73999999999998, "end": 246.79999999999998, "text": "This particular one, the 4N25, is rated at 30 volts."}, {"start": 246.89999999999998, "end": 252.11999999999998, "text": "I'm referring to the detector transistor at 150 milliamps."}, {"start": 252.38, "end": 253.78, "text": "Not a lot of power."}, {"start": 253.78, "end": 257.76, "text": "All right."}, {"start": 257.88, "end": 262.8, "text": "What we have done here is here is our 4N25 optocoupler."}, {"start": 263.28, "end": 266.8, "text": "We have connected it off to 24 volts VCC."}, {"start": 268.44, "end": 271.22, "text": "And through the collector and through the emitter,"}, {"start": 271.38, "end": 275.78, "text": "we've connected a 1K resistor to the base of a TIP120."}, {"start": 275.78, "end": 282.15999999999997, "text": "This is a power Darlington transistor rated, I think, at 5 amps."}, {"start": 282.73999999999995, "end": 287.26, "text": "When I have a high on the LED, it switches on."}, {"start": 287.35999999999996, "end": 290.76, "text": "It switches on the detector transistor,"}, {"start": 291.44, "end": 295.91999999999996, "text": "creates a base emitter current flow through the transistor,"}, {"start": 296.17999999999995, "end": 298.17999999999995, "text": "and switches on the lamp."}, {"start": 298.26, "end": 299.9, "text": "In this case, a light bulb."}, {"start": 299.9, "end": 306.67999999999995, "text": "Here is another variation of the same circuit,"}, {"start": 306.78, "end": 313.35999999999996, "text": "except this time we are using a PNP Darlington transistor,"}, {"start": 313.56, "end": 315.34, "text": "such as a TIP125."}, {"start": 316.62, "end": 319.44, "text": "Notice something different about this circuit"}, {"start": 319.44, "end": 321.34, "text": "as opposed to the previous circuit."}, {"start": 322.79999999999995, "end": 328.15999999999997, "text": "This circuit had the same electrical ground on the microcontroller,"}, {"start": 328.16, "end": 332.88000000000005, "text": "and the secondary output at the 24 volts."}, {"start": 334.0, "end": 339.12, "text": "Here, we have completely severed the secondary power supply totally"}, {"start": 339.12, "end": 341.06, "text": "from the microprocessor."}, {"start": 341.26000000000005, "end": 343.18, "text": "There is no electrical connection."}, {"start": 343.34000000000003, "end": 345.78000000000003, "text": "There is only a light connection."}, {"start": 346.36, "end": 349.08000000000004, "text": "Again, I could have done this very same thing"}, {"start": 349.08000000000004, "end": 352.86, "text": "with the NPN Darlington that we saw earlier."}, {"start": 353.34000000000003, "end": 357.06, "text": "A variation of this is called a solid-state relay."}, {"start": 358.16, "end": 362.04, "text": "And can use a plain old PNP transistor if you want to."}, {"start": 364.0, "end": 365.96000000000004, "text": "Here is another variation,"}, {"start": 366.72, "end": 370.52000000000004, "text": "using this time an N-channel MOSFET."}, {"start": 370.98, "end": 372.5, "text": "What am I doing here?"}, {"start": 372.6, "end": 377.26000000000005, "text": "I'm using the 4N25 when I switch it on"}, {"start": 377.26, "end": 382.3, "text": "to apply voltage to the gate of Q1, the MOSFET."}, {"start": 382.48, "end": 384.71999999999997, "text": "It will immediately turn it on."}, {"start": 385.21999999999997, "end": 388.21999999999997, "text": "It will create a current path and light up the light bulb."}, {"start": 388.56, "end": 389.38, "text": "It's that simple."}, {"start": 390.18, "end": 391.65999999999997, "text": "Be careful, though."}, {"start": 391.94, "end": 394.5, "text": "You need to read the VGS rating,"}, {"start": 394.59999999999997, "end": 396.34, "text": "that's voltage gain source,"}, {"start": 396.59999999999997, "end": 398.96, "text": "in the MOSFET spec sheet."}, {"start": 399.21999999999997, "end": 400.7, "text": "Do not exceed it."}, {"start": 400.7, "end": 403.5, "text": "Most of the ones I use in my videos"}, {"start": 403.5, "end": 405.88, "text": "is rated for right at 24 volts."}, {"start": 406.53999999999996, "end": 408.34, "text": "Don't run them at 24 volts"}, {"start": 408.34, "end": 410.74, "text": "if you're using those particular ones."}, {"start": 410.74, "end": 415.40000000000003, "text": "Here again is,"}, {"start": 416.06, "end": 421.02, "text": "we're using a P-channel power MOSFET"}, {"start": 421.02, "end": 422.56, "text": "as opposed to an N-channel."}, {"start": 422.88, "end": 425.2, "text": "It's wired differently, of course."}, {"start": 425.40000000000003, "end": 426.44, "text": "What I have to do is,"}, {"start": 426.52, "end": 430.82, "text": "I'm using the detector and the MOSFET,"}, {"start": 430.90000000000003, "end": 432.26, "text": "and the optocoupler,"}, {"start": 432.58, "end": 435.76, "text": "to drop the gate voltage to about a half a volt"}, {"start": 435.76, "end": 437.52, "text": "when it switches on."}, {"start": 437.52, "end": 442.74, "text": "And this will create a difference of around 10, 11 volts"}, {"start": 442.74, "end": 444.15999999999997, "text": "between gate and source."}, {"start": 444.38, "end": 445.88, "text": "It will switch on the transistor,"}, {"start": 446.15999999999997, "end": 447.76, "text": "and the light bulb will light up."}, {"start": 448.24, "end": 452.44, "text": "This goes right back to your basic transistor theory."}, {"start": 456.06, "end": 461.52, "text": "Here is another variation of using an optocoupler."}, {"start": 462.32, "end": 463.94, "text": "This time we're going to use it,"}, {"start": 463.94, "end": 469.26, "text": "connect the collector of the optocoupler detector"}, {"start": 469.26, "end": 471.66, "text": "right to the collector of the transistor."}, {"start": 472.78, "end": 473.26, "text": "And of course,"}, {"start": 473.38, "end": 475.28, "text": "the emitter through a 1K resistor"}, {"start": 475.28, "end": 477.98, "text": "is going to switch on Q1."}, {"start": 479.0, "end": 481.32, "text": "This is really a solid state relay."}, {"start": 481.5, "end": 482.48, "text": "I use this"}, {"start": 482.48, "end": 486.34, "text": "in several of my other projects and videos."}, {"start": 486.34, "end": 490.56, "text": "Note something with all of these circuits"}, {"start": 490.56, "end": 491.85999999999996, "text": "that I've just went through."}, {"start": 492.0, "end": 495.02, "text": "Unless you've put capacitors or something in them,"}, {"start": 495.35999999999996, "end": 497.64, "text": "you can pulse width modulate them."}, {"start": 498.26, "end": 500.64, "text": "So I can use this as a switch"}, {"start": 500.64, "end": 504.34, "text": "in either the high side or low side of a load,"}, {"start": 504.44, "end": 507.23999999999995, "text": "and I can pulse width modulated if I want to."}, {"start": 507.24, "end": 515.14, "text": "This shows you the current flow here."}, {"start": 515.28, "end": 516.46, "text": "This switches on."}, {"start": 517.36, "end": 519.3, "text": "Get the base current here."}, {"start": 519.4, "end": 520.14, "text": "Switches on."}, {"start": 520.24, "end": 522.9, "text": "I get the collector current."}, {"start": 523.08, "end": 525.6800000000001, "text": "Actually, it's IE, not IC,"}, {"start": 526.1800000000001, "end": 528.08, "text": "but they're pretty much the same thing."}, {"start": 530.52, "end": 532.1, "text": "This gives you an illustration"}, {"start": 532.1, "end": 534.32, "text": "of how it works in loads."}, {"start": 534.32, "end": 537.6400000000001, "text": "This could easily have been"}, {"start": 537.6400000000001, "end": 540.74, "text": "a push-button switch that you see here."}, {"start": 541.2800000000001, "end": 542.5, "text": "Here is our motor."}, {"start": 543.1400000000001, "end": 545.94, "text": "Here is our common for the power supply."}, {"start": 546.88, "end": 548.58, "text": "You notice that I can place"}, {"start": 548.58, "end": 552.5600000000001, "text": "the transistor collector emitter"}, {"start": 552.5600000000001, "end": 555.46, "text": "from the previous circuit here."}, {"start": 556.2, "end": 559.1600000000001, "text": "I can place it on the ground side."}, {"start": 559.72, "end": 562.6600000000001, "text": "I can place it on the high or VCC side"}, {"start": 562.66, "end": 566.3, "text": "as long as I observe polarity."}, {"start": 568.18, "end": 571.4399999999999, "text": "And it works just like a push-button switch,"}, {"start": 571.48, "end": 573.3399999999999, "text": "and all of this is isolated"}, {"start": 573.3399999999999, "end": 575.3399999999999, "text": "from your microcontroller."}, {"start": 575.9, "end": 577.92, "text": "Boy, that makes things a lot easier."}, {"start": 580.6999999999999, "end": 584.3, "text": "Here is a, I guess you could say,"}, {"start": 584.4399999999999, "end": 586.1999999999999, "text": "it's a fairly well-complete"}, {"start": 586.1999999999999, "end": 588.6999999999999, "text": "solid-state DC relay."}, {"start": 588.7, "end": 590.5200000000001, "text": "Here is the protection circuit"}, {"start": 590.5200000000001, "end": 591.8000000000001, "text": "we talked about earlier."}, {"start": 592.1600000000001, "end": 593.9200000000001, "text": "Here is our optocoupler,"}, {"start": 594.26, "end": 596.38, "text": "and here is our transistor switch."}, {"start": 597.5400000000001, "end": 599.2800000000001, "text": "These, I have built this."}, {"start": 599.36, "end": 600.46, "text": "It works just fine."}, {"start": 603.5600000000001, "end": 605.7, "text": "All right, here's another variation"}, {"start": 605.7, "end": 606.9200000000001, "text": "of an optocoupler,"}, {"start": 607.08, "end": 609.12, "text": "but I won't go much into these."}, {"start": 609.12, "end": 613.1, "text": "They use phototriax or photodiax,"}, {"start": 613.22, "end": 615.24, "text": "and they are used with triax"}, {"start": 615.24, "end": 617.72, "text": "and or SCRs"}, {"start": 617.72, "end": 621.26, "text": "to create solid-state AC relays."}, {"start": 622.26, "end": 624.1, "text": "That's going to be a different video,"}, {"start": 624.44, "end": 626.38, "text": "but it's pretty much the same circuit"}, {"start": 626.38, "end": 627.66, "text": "on the left side,"}, {"start": 628.4, "end": 629.82, "text": "and we will go over"}, {"start": 629.82, "end": 633.04, "text": "how triax and SCRs work"}, {"start": 633.04, "end": 634.46, "text": "in separate videos."}, {"start": 634.46, "end": 639.24, "text": "And that's this brief introduction"}, {"start": 639.24, "end": 641.46, "text": "to optocouplers."}, {"start": 642.6800000000001, "end": 644.46, "text": "My website has a whole page"}, {"start": 644.98, "end": 646.08, "text": "of circuit examples"}, {"start": 646.08, "end": 647.82, "text": "and what we just went over."}, {"start": 648.5400000000001, "end": 649.46, "text": "And now let's watch"}, {"start": 649.46, "end": 651.1, "text": "a couple of short video clips"}, {"start": 651.1, "end": 652.5, "text": "that I added onto this"}, {"start": 652.5, "end": 654.74, "text": "using optocouplers"}, {"start": 654.74, "end": 659.34, "text": "to control lights and motors"}, {"start": 659.34, "end": 661.52, "text": "and various other devices."}, {"start": 661.52, "end": 666.76, "text": "Anyway, let's give this"}, {"start": 666.76, "end": 667.76, "text": "a little test run"}, {"start": 667.76, "end": 669.92, "text": "just to let you see"}, {"start": 669.92, "end": 670.62, "text": "what it can do."}, {"start": 671.0799999999999, "end": 672.0799999999999, "text": "Power is on."}, {"start": 672.1999999999999, "end": 673.04, "text": "You notice I got a little"}, {"start": 673.04, "end": 676.28, "text": "sort of alt-UV LED down there."}, {"start": 676.42, "end": 677.9, "text": "Hey, they're useful for something."}, {"start": 678.8199999999999, "end": 680.76, "text": "This is designed to be later on"}, {"start": 680.76, "end": 683.3199999999999, "text": "to operate an H-bridge,"}, {"start": 683.8, "end": 685.54, "text": "but what I want to do"}, {"start": 685.54, "end": 687.76, "text": "is just, if you look out here,"}, {"start": 687.8199999999999, "end": 689.3199999999999, "text": "you'll see an LED come on,"}, {"start": 689.32, "end": 691.7800000000001, "text": "and you'll notice"}, {"start": 691.7800000000001, "end": 692.6600000000001, "text": "this lights up."}, {"start": 692.74, "end": 694.4200000000001, "text": "This is just an LED across."}, {"start": 695.1800000000001, "end": 696.0200000000001, "text": "What I'm doing"}, {"start": 696.0200000000001, "end": 697.3000000000001, "text": "is reading one of the,"}, {"start": 697.4200000000001, "end": 700.1800000000001, "text": "is analog input channel."}, {"start": 700.1800000000001, "end": 701.12, "text": "I'm reading the value"}, {"start": 701.12, "end": 701.96, "text": "on this pot"}, {"start": 701.96, "end": 705.1800000000001, "text": "to control the pulse width"}, {"start": 705.1800000000001, "end": 706.2800000000001, "text": "modulation out."}, {"start": 707.82, "end": 710.1800000000001, "text": "I can control it on and off."}, {"start": 710.2800000000001, "end": 711.32, "text": "Now, the trick is"}, {"start": 711.32, "end": 713.22, "text": "when I program"}, {"start": 713.22, "end": 715.0200000000001, "text": "this particular PIC chip,"}, {"start": 715.02, "end": 716.8199999999999, "text": "that if either,"}, {"start": 717.06, "end": 718.14, "text": "I have to have"}, {"start": 718.14, "end": 720.6, "text": "both,"}, {"start": 721.14, "end": 722.74, "text": "either one or the other"}, {"start": 722.74, "end": 723.86, "text": "outputs on."}, {"start": 723.96, "end": 724.88, "text": "You'll see it over there"}, {"start": 724.88, "end": 725.76, "text": "is the green one."}, {"start": 727.22, "end": 728.0799999999999, "text": "I got to have"}, {"start": 728.0799999999999, "end": 729.5, "text": "one or the other on."}, {"start": 729.96, "end": 730.66, "text": "It's programmed"}, {"start": 730.66, "end": 732.12, "text": "to kill the pulse width"}, {"start": 732.12, "end": 733.24, "text": "modulation out"}, {"start": 733.24, "end": 734.84, "text": "if none of the other"}, {"start": 734.84, "end": 736.1999999999999, "text": "two outputs are working."}, {"start": 736.34, "end": 737.06, "text": "Those will later"}, {"start": 737.06, "end": 738.66, "text": "go on to an H-bridge"}, {"start": 738.66, "end": 739.76, "text": "that I will demonstrate."}, {"start": 741.5799999999999, "end": 742.8199999999999, "text": "Nothing much here."}, {"start": 742.82, "end": 745.9200000000001, "text": "It works,"}, {"start": 746.08, "end": 747.7, "text": "it seems quite well."}, {"start": 751.86, "end": 753.48, "text": "If you look further up,"}, {"start": 753.5200000000001, "end": 755.4000000000001, "text": "it has a 12 volt power supply."}, {"start": 755.72, "end": 757.32, "text": "The important part"}, {"start": 757.32, "end": 758.96, "text": "to note in this circuit"}, {"start": 758.96, "end": 766.58, "text": "is the opto isolator here."}, {"start": 766.7800000000001, "end": 768.12, "text": "Everything on that side"}, {"start": 768.12, "end": 769.2800000000001, "text": "of the opto isolator"}, {"start": 769.2800000000001, "end": 770.3800000000001, "text": "is 5 volts."}, {"start": 770.38, "end": 772.2, "text": "Everything on this side,"}, {"start": 772.34, "end": 773.06, "text": "here, here,"}, {"start": 773.18, "end": 774.16, "text": "back through there,"}, {"start": 774.5, "end": 776.52, "text": "is 12 volts."}, {"start": 777.64, "end": 779.08, "text": "So I can have"}, {"start": 779.08, "end": 780.4, "text": "really nice control"}, {"start": 780.4, "end": 781.98, "text": "of higher voltage circuits"}, {"start": 781.98, "end": 783.7, "text": "by using an opto coupler."}, {"start": 785.4399999999999, "end": 787.08, "text": "Again, here is an overall"}, {"start": 787.08, "end": 788.56, "text": "picture of it once again."}, {"start": 792.96, "end": 794.0, "text": "And you can see"}, {"start": 794.0, "end": 794.92, "text": "the light bars"}, {"start": 794.92, "end": 795.98, "text": "go on and off"}, {"start": 795.98, "end": 797.28, "text": "depending on polarity."}, {"start": 797.28, "end": 799.56, "text": "The important part"}, {"start": 799.56, "end": 800.62, "text": "about this is"}, {"start": 800.62, "end": 802.48, "text": "is all this"}, {"start": 802.48, "end": 803.9, "text": "12 volt circuitry"}, {"start": 803.9, "end": 804.4399999999999, "text": "over here,"}, {"start": 804.54, "end": 805.04, "text": "the motor,"}, {"start": 805.56, "end": 806.0799999999999, "text": "the H-bridge"}, {"start": 806.0799999999999, "end": 807.14, "text": "is only a section"}, {"start": 807.14, "end": 807.92, "text": "of this board,"}, {"start": 808.0, "end": 808.62, "text": "by the way."}, {"start": 809.16, "end": 811.0799999999999, "text": "The power control circuit,"}, {"start": 811.5799999999999, "end": 812.3399999999999, "text": "the H-bridge,"}, {"start": 812.48, "end": 813.02, "text": "the motor,"}, {"start": 813.4, "end": 814.48, "text": "all of this stuff"}, {"start": 814.48, "end": 816.68, "text": "is completely isolated"}, {"start": 816.68, "end": 818.5799999999999, "text": "from all the 5 volt circuitry"}, {"start": 818.5799999999999, "end": 819.24, "text": "on the pick"}, {"start": 819.24, "end": 820.04, "text": "or Arduino"}, {"start": 820.04, "end": 821.5, "text": "or whatever you're using."}, {"start": 827.28, "end": 831.06, "text": "of this"}, {"start": 833.5, "end": 834.38, "text": "a little bit"}, {"start": 834.38, "end": 835.06, "text": "over here."}, {"start": 835.26, "end": 835.92, "text": "Now I'll show you"}, {"start": 835.92, "end": 837.88, "text": "how it plиль"}, {"start": 837.92, "end": 838.16, "text": "behind to flash"}, {"start": 838.16, "end": 840.5799999999999, "text": "in the end"}, {"start": 840.5799999999999, "end": 840.6, "text": "here."}, {"start": 840.66, "end": 842.8, "text": "Of course,"}, {"start": 842.9599999999999, "end": 843.06, "text": "the wind"}, {"start": 843.06, "end": 844.02, "text": "can be"}, {"start": 844.02, "end": 844.4399999999999, "text": "fen Grü"}, {"start": 844.4399999999999, "end": 845.76, "text": "ow"}, {"start": 845.76, "end": 845.9599999999999, "text": "아무�'t"}, {"start": 845.9599999999999, "end": 848.06, "text": "how the"}, {"start": 848.06, "end": 849.88, "text": "on by way."}]}